definition.value: The S-(4-coumaroyl) derivative of coenzyme A.
A hydroxybenzoyl-CoA that is the S-(4-hydroxybenzoyl) derivative of coenzyme A.
An acyl-CoA resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxylic acid group of 5-hydroxypentanoic acid.
An acyl-CoA that is the S-(5-hydroxythiophene-2-carbonyl) derivative of coenzyme A.
